adjectives.description: tricklike (comparative more tricklike, superlative most tricklike)

entries.meaning: Resembling or characteristic of a trick.
examples: The anecdotes they coin, whether in half-hearted travelogues or in cynical Benetton catalogues, invoke that developmental schema to recapitulate the West's erstwhile commodity enchantment through its tricklike discovery in the past-as-present eyes of the enchanted Other.
